article.headline: Oral Roberts 80, Ark.-Pine Bluff 44
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- Warren Niles and Dominique Morrison scored 19 points each to lead Oral Roberts to an 80-44 victory over Arkansas-Pine Bluff in a consolation game of the NIT Season Tip-Off on Wednesday night. Michael Craion had 17 points and Steven Roundtree 11 for the Golden Eagles (1-2). Craion added eight rebounds. Savalace Townsend scored 16 points to lead the Golden Lions (0-2). Oral Roberts never trailed, led 33-15 at halftime and padded its cushion to 42 points in the second half. The Golden Eagles shot 52.9 percent (27 for 51) from the floor and enjoyed a 34-19 rebounding edge.
